Data: Stanlake to Guptill, 2 wide short outside off, swings away as Guptill chases it, Alex Carey is also on the move and the ball ends up at third man for a couple of extras
Stanlake to Munro, no run fullish, 142kph outside off, driven without timing to point
Stanlake to Munro, 1 leg bye fired into the pads, Munro looks for his favoured leg-side pick up but doesn't connect... pitched outside, I think
Stanlake to Guptill, no run short of a length, 142kph and swerving away as Guptill wafts a cut without foot movement and is beaten
Stanlake to Guptill, 1 run angled in straight, 146kph/90mph and dabbed down into the leg side for one

Stanlake to Munro, SIX runs full, heaved to leg... and into the crowd! Munro clears the pickets for the first time, looked a bit of a mishit as the ball ballooned into the sky, but it had the legs to go all the way. And one of the orangemen in the crowd missed his chance of $50,000, too! Completely misjudged it
Stanlake to Munro, 1 wide short, slightly leg side, wide again
Stanlake to Munro, 1 run pitched up and driven, they take on Warner's arm at mid-off... but the throw is wide
Kane Richardson to Munro, 1 run length, 134kph and shaping a touch on middle and leg, Munro dabs wide of mid-on
Kane Richardson to Guptill, no run slightly short of a length in the channel, maybe stays a bit low and Guptill fails to connect
Kane Richardson to Guptill, FOUR runs pitched up and smeared back down the ground, whacked past mid-off for four!
Kane Richardson to Guptill, no run length delivery outside off, punched square
Kane Richardson to Guptill, FOUR runs drifting into the pads, Guptill just needs to get a tickle on it, past Carey and away to fine leg
Kane Richardson to Guptill, 1 run full, comes on to the front foot and prods towards extra cover for a scampered one
Tye to Guptill, 1 run pitched up on middle and off, pushed through mid-on
Tye to Munro, FOUR runs angled across, 133kph and Munro swaps power for placement, a deft guide past gully for four
Tye to Munro, FOUR runs short ball on the hip, Munro twocks it in front of square, superb timing and it races to the rope, beating the dive of man running up from deep square
Tye to Munro, FOUR runs pitched up and cracked over cover this time! Three fours in a row for Munro, stepping out to carve a lofted drive
Tye to Munro, 1 run outside off, maybe taking the pace off, punched to cover
Tye to Guptill, 1 run length, 125kph and angling in, dabbed wide of the bowler in his follow through and they trot the single
Agar to Guptill, SIX runs tossed up and spanked back over long-on first ball! Guptill steps out and climbs into the spin, only just clears the short, straight boundary
Agar to Guptill, no run dragged down, rocks back and bottom-edges a pull
Agar to Guptill, 1 run fired in straight and worked for one
Agar to Munro, 1 run full, 104kph wide of leg stump, Munro chops it through midwicket
Agar to Guptill, 1 run flat, skidding on as Guptill plays back, bottom-edged on the cut for one
Agar to Munro, no run darted outside leg stump again and this time Munro tries to reverse-slog over cover, gets an inside edge into his pads
Stanlake to Guptill, 1 run full and straight, Guptill launches at it, gets a thick inside edge on to his boot
Stanlake to Munro, 1 run back of a length, Munro pulls powerfully but flat, just one to deep square leg

Stanlake to Guptill, OUT got him, toe-ended to mid-off! Backed away to try and thrash down the ground, completely mistimed and Warner revs the chainsaw in celebration. Stanlake with the breakthrough, Guptill goes (relatively) cheaply this time
Stanlake to Williamson, 1 wide attempted yorker, 146kph and squirming past the pads, nearly had Williamson off his feet - a touch leg side, though, a called wide
Stanlake to Williamson, no run comes across and pokes into the covers
Stanlake to Williamson, FOUR runs short of a length, slapped through cover point, that'll get him going... NZ raise 50 in the fifth over
Stanlake to Williamson, no run full in the channel, 142kph and Williamson leans into a classy-looking cover drive, picks out the fielder
Kane Richardson to Munro, SIX runs skips out, clumped down the ground - sails over long-on! Didn't quite get hold of it but on this ground, that's six

Kane Richardson to Munro, OUT straight up this time, and taken at mid-on! Munro holes out, Agar pouching it safely as Richardson gives it the double-fist pump. Maybe a bit of pace off there... NZ momentum well and truly checked now
Kane Richardson to Chapman, no run short of a length, rising up to be blocked back in the crease
Kane Richardson to Chapman, no run angled across around off, tapped away
Kane Richardson to Chapman, no run back of a length, 133kph and into the back pad, Chapman nudging across the line... High, I reckon
Kane Richardson to Chapman, FOUR runs short and wide and lashed for four! Bit of room for the dinky dasher to throw his hands through the cut, gets it away
Stoinis to Williamson, no run full, fourth-stump line, driven to cover on the bounce
Stoinis to Williamson, 1 run dabbed into the covers, the throw to the non-striker's end flies away, but there's a man backing up eventually
Stoinis to Chapman, 1 run back of a length outside off, swatted down the ground to long-off
Stoinis to Williamson, 1 run short, 125kph and Williamson whirls on a pull, gets it past the dive of midwicket
Stoinis to Chapman, no run on the stumps, clipped to midwicket
Stoinis to Chapman, 2 runs slower delivery, Chapman gets his pull past the ring this time and Williamson hares back to the danger end to make sure of two
Agar to Williamson, 1 run lobbed up from round the wicket, nurdled towards wide long-on, just a single there
Agar to Chapman, 1 run flat on middle and leg, clipped through midwicket
Agar to Williamson, 2 runs floated up full and Williamson works it into the gap this time, Warner has to run across from long-on and they hustle back for two

Agar to Williamson, OUT timber! Tossed up by Agar, gets him trying to come down the ground, nowhere near the pitch and an ugly swipe leaves Williamson stranded, the ball thudding into off stump! Nicely bowled, this wasn't a dart - gave it some air and duped the batsman
Agar to Taylor, 1 run flighted, Taylor comes out and turns it into a full toss, clipped square for one

Agar to Chapman, OUT tossed up and Chapman attempts to sweep, hit on the front pad - and given! After a moment's discussion, he decides to review, however... Looked pretty good to me, but maybe going on with the angle from round the wicket? No bat involved, it pitched in line and ball-tracking says it would have smashed off stump! Good
Stanlake to Taylor, 2 runs full and straight and whipped off the toes, Chris Lynn moves across from midwicket and dives to try and cut it off... and he's hurt here, going to need some treatment
Stanlake to Taylor, 1 run short outside off, cut firmly to the sweeper
Stanlake to de Grandhomme, 2 runs length outside off, De Grandhomme sits back and guides a couple wide of third man
Stanlake to de Grandhomme, 2 runs dug in, 140kph and he pulls, off the splice into a gap at midwicket for a couple
Stanlake to de Grandhomme, FOUR runs short again, De Grandhomme latches on this time and blitzes a pull up and over the ring, wide of long-on for four
Stanlake to de Grandhomme, 1 run dabbed to short third man, CDG turns to regain his ground as the throw comes in, then they trot the one
Agar to de Grandhomme, 1 run tossed up on off and punched down the ground
Agar to Taylor, FOUR runs gets a touch too straight and Taylor glides it off his pads, gets it very fine and it runs away to the rope for four
Agar to Taylor, no run pushed through on leg stump, blocked
Agar to Taylor, 1 run floated up, worked down the ground

Agar to de Grandhomme, OUT baits the hook, De Grandhomme bites... picks out cow corner! No great connection and there's a man out there waiting, the safe hands of Glenn Maxwell and Agar has a third wicket! Really not though through, that shot... NZ five down
Agar to Taylor, 1 run fired into the toes, clipped through midwicket for one
Stoinis to Taylor, no run full, maybe a slower ball, skids through under the bat outside off
Stoinis to Taylor, 1 run pitched up straight and worked into the leg side
Stoinis to Seifert, no run back of a length, 128kph outside off and Seifert cuts firmly but picks out backward point

Stoinis to Seifert, OUT bowled 'im! Slips in the yorker again, seemed to go under the bat - in fact, Seifert just played the wrong line - and the ball thudded into the base of off stump. Good bowling, Australia applying the chokehold here
Stoinis to Southee, 1 run fired in and dinked for one
Stoinis to Taylor, 1 run short ball, at the body, Taylor pulls but doesn't get hold of it
Kane Richardson to Taylor, 2 runs back of a length and worked from off stump to midwicket, Richardson has to give chase and they hurry back for two
Kane Richardson to Taylor, 1 run angled in and worked to leg again, this time long-on comes in to prevent a second
Kane Richardson to Southee, FOUR runs full ball, clipped firmly off the pads, beats the diving attempt on the rope and that's a welcome boundary

Kane Richardson to Southee, OUT slower ball, Southee heaves to leg - picks out deep midwicket! Another dumb slog without the air and it plops into the hands of Maxwell running in, took it low, took it well
Kane Richardson to Taylor, 1 run full on the stumps, nudged into the gap at midwicket
Kane Richardson to Sodhi, no run short of a length, 139kph and Sodhi defends down to the leg side
Tye to Taylor, 2 runs full on the toes and Taylor nurdles into the leg side, they scamper hard for two
Tye to Taylor, 1 leg bye full, taking the pace off hits the pad and runs square
Tye to Sodhi, no run full, 137kph outside off and chopped towards point
Tye to Sodhi, no run slower delivery this time, slips through outside the line of off
Tye to Sodhi, 1 run full and straight, taking the pace off again, gets bat on it into the leg side
Tye to Taylor, 1 run length outside off, Taylor cuts into the ground behind point for one
Stoinis to Taylor, 1 run pitched up and driven for one to the edge of the ring
Stoinis to Sodhi, 1 run full toss, Sodhi taps it down into the off side, Taylor is quickly on the move as backward point fires in the throw
Stoinis to Taylor, no run goes for the yorker again, 130kph cross-seam, Taylor chops down on it
Stoinis to Taylor, 1 run slower ball, cut into the ground behind point, Richardson throws himself after it to keep them to one
Stoinis to Sodhi, no run pitched up, 130kph/80mph and drilled back to the bowler in his follow through
Stoinis to Sodhi, 1 run short and wide and clubbed, they take the single to deep cover
Stanlake to Sodhi, no run shortish, 137kph outside off, defended from the crease
Stanlake to Sodhi, 1 run straighter line and Sodhi clips a single to get Taylor on strike

Stanlake to Taylor, FOUR runs short, wide and slashed past backward point! Travis Head, on as a sub fielder, nearly gets fingertips on it but the ball zips by and away to the rope for a first boundary in a while
Stanlake to Taylor, 1 run this comes back in and hits the gloves as Taylor goes to cut again
Stanlake to Sodhi, no run banged in, good bumper to a No. 10, he flinches out of the way
Stanlake to Sodhi, 1 run length outside off, 141kph, steered down to third man
Kane Richardson to Sodhi, no run full and straight and tapped back, Richardson comes down to field
Kane Richardson to Sodhi, 1 run slower ball, goes back outside off and guides it wide of short third man for one
Kane Richardson to Taylor, no run full outside off, 134kph and Taylor goes for the cow-corner mow, ends up toeing it back to the bowler
Kane Richardson to Taylor, no run another dot, slow floater outside off and this induces a big swing and miss
Kane Richardson to Taylor, no run fullish, pace off again, Taylor heaves across the line and fails to connect
Kane Richardson to Taylor, 1 run pitched up and clubbed to leg, just one to the man on the boundary square
Tye to Taylor, 1 run full on the stumps, worked back down the ground to long-on
Tye to Santner, OUT short and leg side, flies through as Santner pulls - was there glove on it? Yes! Tye banged in a fast bumper, Australia celebrated immediately and up went the finger. Oh dear
Tye to Seifert, no run takes the pace off, defended on off stump
Tye to Seifert, no run angled in on the stumps and worked to leg
Tye to Seifert, no run short, 130kph outside off and rising through as Seifert ignores it
Tye to Seifert, 1 run slower delivery on off, pushed into the covers for one to get off the mark
Agar to Seifert, 1 run angled in with the arm from round the wicket, worked to leg for a single
Agar to Taylor, no run floated up full and clipped back to the bowler
Agar to Taylor, 2 runs gives it some air, nudged into a gap at midwicket and they scamper the two
Agar to Taylor, 1 run wheels away on middle and leg, clipped in front of square and Agar chases after it
Agar to Seifert, 1 run flat, quicker ball, worked to leg again and Seifert has to gets his skates on
Agar to Taylor, 1 run fired in and flicked to midwicket, just the one this time, brings up the NZ 100. Terrific figures for Agar, his best in T20Is
Stoinis to Taylor, SIX runs in the slot, pounded down the ground for six! Hello, my old friend... Taylor picks this and blooters it over long-on, NZ will take a couple more of those!
Stoinis to Taylor, no run short, slower delivery and Taylor is hit on the body, Sodhi then has to throw himself back in as Stoinis fields and throws for the stumps
Stoinis to Taylor, no run full, taking the pace off, again Taylor doesn't connect with a big mow across the line
Stoinis to Taylor, 2 runs pitched up and squirted into the leg side, Taylor is struggling to get back here... but Tye's throw is poor and Carey can't collect properly!
Stoinis to Taylor, 1 wide banged in as Taylor steps out, that's in a different post code on height
Stoinis to Taylor, 2 runs short ball outside off, Taylor creams a pull wide of long-on, Agar dives to cut it off but they come back for two
Stoinis to Taylor, no run slower delivery, wide of the stumps, another swing and miss
Tye to Sodhi, SIX runs full, slower ball, Sodhi spots it - and booms six more over long-on! Hefty whack and it goes waaaaay back into the crowd! Good start
Tye to Sodhi, 1 run full toss, swatted into the leg side for one
Tye to Taylor, 1 run full and wide, 136kph and Taylor can only squeeze it to backward point as he advanced down the pitch
Tye to Sodhi, OUT castled! Sodhi makes room and heaves across the line, Tye hits the top of middle! Sodhi runs straight off, he's done his job
Tye to Boult, 1 run full toss on off, Boult bunts it down the ground to bring Taylor on strike

Tye to Taylor, 1 leg bye banged in, 135kph and Taylor pulls like a lusty stevedore, takes it on the helmet, just a single to backward point! It's not much more than a hill of beans but Taylor has at least given NZ something to bowl at

8.35pm: Is that enough for a game? NZ struggled, despite another lively opening. The pitch looked a little more difficult to time the ball on, but David Warner shuffled his attack brilliantly and, after Guptll and Munro fell in succession, NZ just couldn't get going. Ross Taylor battled manfully but you'd back Australia to blast their way to
Right, the teams are back. Here's Trent Boult, armed with the new ball
Boult to Warner, no run full and straight, a hint of swing, tight line to the left-hander. A solid start
Boult to Warner, FOUR runs slightly back of a length this time, and hauled imperiously through midwicket! He timed the pants off that, with no apparent room to do so
Boult to Warner, 2 runs fuller this time, but wide of off stump, Warner frees his arms and launches a mistimed drive over the covers. It plugs beyond the fielder and is gathered inside the rope
Boult to Warner, no run full and swinging, defended with caution back down the pitch
Boult to Warner, no run stabbed into the covers
Boult to Warner, no run full again, squeezed into the off side
Sodhi to Short, no run looped up onto a good length, and dabbed back down the pitch
Sodhi to Short, no run back of a length, tight line, flicked into the leg side
Sodhi to Short, no run down on one knee for the slog sweep, strikes the pad but that pitched outside leg
Sodhi to Short, FOUR runs that's a tremendous glide through third man, picking the legbreak and sliding it through the gap with an open face
Sodhi to Short, 1 run nudged off the pads to backward square
Sodhi to Warner, no run pushed onto the back foot, defended back down the pitch, that's a tidy over
Southee to Short, 1 run full length, but sliding into the pads, tucked to deep backward square
Southee to Warner, 1 run worked off the legs once more, a big stretch at backward square to intercept
Southee to Short, 2 runs flashed into the leg side
Southee to Short, no run smashed hard down the ground, but he's miscued it, and Williamson at mid-off can't reach it! He was back on his heels, perhaps expecting the ball to come harder and faster
Southee to Short, 1 run bunted out to deep midwicket
Southee to Warner, 1 run thrashed to deep point
Sodhi to Warner, 1 run turning into the legs from a good length, flipped off the hip to midwicket
Sodhi to Short, no run more signs of turn from a middle and leg line, constricting Short's free-flowing arms
Sodhi to Short, FOUR runs too short this time, and Short just leans back to slap another four through the off side. Easy peasy
Sodhi to Short, no run on a good length, and tapped back to the bowler
Sodhi to Short, no run a swish across the line but no real contact
Sodhi to Short, 1 run on the back foot, sliding into a back-foot glide to cover
Boult to Short, no run thrashed into the off side, but can't beat the man at mid-off
Boult to Short, FOUR runs that's a pounding shot. Overpitched from Boult, an attempted yorker, but ended up right in Short's arc, and was flashed back with interest just past the stumps
Boult to Short, FOUR runs same again! In the slot, and slotted down the ground. Top biffing
Boult to Short, 1 run on the back foot this time, stabbed to cover and they scuttle the run
Boult to Warner, 1 run worked out to short midwicket
Boult to Short, SIX runs hoisted off the back foot, high and handsome over the leg side! Boult's length, short and full, has been picked off in this over, and Australia are stomping into command now
Southee to Warner, 1 run stand and deliver, Warner goes for the big wind-up, under-edges a pull into the crease, but they steal the single anyway
Southee to Short, SIX runs on the pads, and ping! Into the stands over square leg. That was effortless, and huge!
Southee to Short, SIX runs slammed into the stands! Back to back sixes, and this one is a murderous mow, through the line and over long-on!
Southee to Short, 1 leg bye winding up for another big hit, but this time strikes the pads
Southee to Warner, 2 runs good effort from the keeper to take the sting out of a leg glance, but more runs...
Southee to Warner, no run a short-arm jab, into the leg side
Santner to Short, no run on the pads, clipped to mid-on
Santner to Short, 1 run round the wicket, looped up and dipping into the toes, flicked to leg
Santner to Warner, 1 run tapped into the leg side once more
Santner to Short, FOUR runs tossed out wide, there's room to free the arms and that is powered through the covers. In the air for a time, but just too much oomph to intercept
Santner to Short, no run punched down the ground
Santner to Short, no run tapped into the off side
Munro to Warner, FOUR runs round the wicket, hauled through the gap at midiwicket!
Munro to Warner, 2 runs back of a length, stabbed into the covers
Munro to Warner, 1 run banged in short, hoisted over backward square leg, and that is an outstanding one-handed grab to cut off the four!
Munro to Short, FOUR runs another murderous pull, and this time the same fielder, de Grandhomme, is nutmegged! Up comes a very brisk fifty
Munro to Short, no run a mistimed cut
Santner to Agar, no run nudged to leg
Santner to Agar, 1 run on the toes, clipped firmly to the leg side, he's looking for two and has to scuttle back as Munro swoops and sends in the shy
Santner to Warner, 2 runs flicked to the leg side once more
Santner to Warner, no run attempted reverse dab, gets in a tangle and topples over as the keeper whips off the bails. The umpires are taking a look but the toe is always anchored over the line
Santner to Warner, 2 runs stabbed off the back foot to cover
Santner to Warner, no run fully forward, poked back to the bowler
Sodhi to Agar, 1 run dances at the crease to make room for a thrash through the covers but can't connect properly
Sodhi to Maxwell, no run crushed into the off side, just short of cover... New Zealand are sensing something here
Sodhi to Maxwell, no run punched to cover, looking for the single but no way through
Sodhi to Maxwell, 1 run squirted into the gap in the covers

Sodhi to Agar, 4 byes a massive wind-up and a missed stumping! A big legbreak, turned through a wild mow across the line, and the keeper was as done in as the batsman ... four byes to add insult to injury
Santner to Maxwell, no run sliding into the legs, can't flick it square
Santner to Maxwell, 1 run worked down to long on
Santner to Finch, 1 run looped up, into the toes, tucked to leg

Santner to Maxwell, 1 run another unhinged swipe through the line, spirals off the toe of the bat, three men circling at backward point, who wants it? No-one gets there! Plugs just out of reach of the diving Ross Taylor ... well now...
Santner to Finch, 2 runs finds the gap at midwicket
Munro to Maxwell, 2 runs worked to the leg side
Munro to Maxwell, 1 run pulled around the corner to backward square leg
Munro to Finch, 1 run on the back foot, nudged to the leg side
Munro to Maxwell, 1 run stabbed down the ground, beats the stretching bowler
Munro to Finch, 1 run flicked off the hip out to deep midwicket
Munro to Maxwell, 1 run back of a length, a bottom-handed bunt out to the leg side
Boult to Maxwell, 2 runs that's a sublime strike, an angled drive into the gap in the covers, timed to perfection, but Southee slides well to intercept just inside the rope
Boult to Maxwell, no run yorker! Well bowled, well dug out
Boult to Maxwell, 1 run a big smear into the leg side from outside off, almost swings himself off his feet in alacrity
Boult to Finch, no run banged in short, an attempted pull, can't connect, and the keeper's shy keeps the non-striker in his place

Boult to Finch, 1 run incredible pick-up from Williamson, but just wide! A tip and run to the covers, Williamson released the ball almost before he had gathered it, and missed the stumps by a whisker!
Boult to Maxwell, 1 run more brilliance on the boundary! De Grandhomme at full stretch saves the four at deep midwicket. New Zealand are brawling...
Sodhi to Maxwell, SIX runs tossed up outside off, Maxwell picks the legbreak, gives himself room, and slams it into the stands at long-off!
Sodhi to Maxwell, 1 run back of a length, slapped hard and low past the bowler
Sodhi to Finch, no run well bowled, Finch gives himself room and Sodhi cramps him with the googly. Cut to point
Sodhi to Finch, no run wider line, Finch goes for another cut but can't make proper contact
Sodhi to Finch, 1 run on the legs, worked around the corner
Sodhi to Maxwell, no run a fast, flat legbreak, Maxwell can't capitalise

Santner to Finch, (no ball) 2 runs a filthy beamer, and a brilliant catch, but it won't count! Slammed out to wide long-on, where the ball is hauled in by Chapman with an excellent relay take, tossing the ball up in mid-air as he clambered back into play
Santner to Finch, 1 run gets away with the free hit
Santner to Maxwell, 1 run
Santner to Finch, 2 runs eased out to midwicket
Santner to Finch, SIX runs muscled over long-on. That's sweet, sweet power
And back comes the rain. Humbug. Hopefully it's just another short interlude

10.17pm I'm afraid it is still hammering down. We could be set for an unsatisfactory conclusion here, but fingers crossed. Australia in utter control of DLS, so it's NZ who need to get back out there and takes lots of wickets
10.26pm The rain appears to have stopped and the mopping-up is underway. Watch this space...

10.38pm MATCH ABANDONED. That's all folks... the umpires have decided that the ground is too wet to resume before the cut-off time. That's a pity, but there's no complaints about the inaugural Trans-Tasman T20 champions. Australia win by 19 runs on DLS, with five wins out of five in the tournament.

Warner, who is set to board a stupid o'clock plane to South Africa tomorrow, collects the T20 Trophy, and that concludes the formalities. Thanks for tuning in - next up, we've got the ODI series between New Zealand and England, starting on Sunday. See you then.
Australia won by 19 runs (D/L method)
Player of the match is Ashton Agar, AUS
